<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-05-18T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-05-18T16:00:00-05:00" n="400" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d400">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">839.51/4389: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in the Dominican, Republic</hi>
                                (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Schoenfeld</hi></persName>)
                                <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Ciudad
                                        Trujillo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-05-18T16:00:00-05:00">May 18, 1936—4
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 6:06 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>13. Department’s instruction No. 427, May 12. Respectfully suggest that
                            text of proposed note to the Dominican Government enclosed with your
                            instruction be reconsidered in the light of my despatches 3280 April 30,
                            3287 May 5, and 3300 May 9<note n="55" xml:id="d400fn55">Despatch No.
                                3287, May 5, not printed.</note> which despatches do not appear to
                            have been before the officers who drafted Department’s instructions.</p>
                        <p>I shall defer delivery of proposed note pending Department’s further
                            instructions.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Schoenfeld</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>